node.text: It's basically like a 12 minute risotto without the need to stir it. The easiest way to get even vegetable resistant kids to WANT to eat them because each bite has confetti like pieces of carrot and broccoli with tons of of flavors in every bite. What other vegetable would you want to add in? 🌶🫑 Recipe link in bio! https://weelicious.com/carrot-broccoli-cheese-orzo/

node.text: What kind of milk do you drink? I started making this homemade milk in different flavors (hello strawberry, chocolate and even green tea 🍵🍓🍫) and its been a game changer. Nothing but super creamy, plant-based milk you can use in cereal, coffee, smoothies, drink on it's own and much more. Recipe on Weelicious! https://weelicious.com/homemade-oat-milk-recipe/

node.text: Now that half of our family is vegetarian, I'm constantly trying to work on flexible recipes to fit everyone's food choices. These tacos are super California fresh and if you've never tried a crispy avocado, your life is about to change! Recipe on Weelicious. https://weelicious.com/whitefish-and-crispy-avocado-tacos-recipe/

node.title: White Fish and Crispy Avocado Tacos!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by WEELICIOUS on August 16, 2021 tagging @billabongwomens, and @islandviewhawaii. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: I’m constantly trying to conquer fears in my life at every level and make sure my kids do too. One of them has been swimming in the ocean with sharks 🦈 Chloe had ZERO desire to try it and was literally shaking when we got into the water, but 5 minutes into the experience relaxed and actually loved it (swipe to watch how fast we moved to get out of their way 😳). We were surrounded by 3 different varieties of sharks and watching them peacefully swim around us made it even more exciting. What fear do you want to conquer?

node.text: We’ve decided that we’re only drinking smoothies out of pineapples from here on out! 🍍Hawaiian EATING and PLAYING tour 2021 continues! Toss out any and all recommendations we shouldn’t miss!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by WEELICIOUS in North Shore, Oahu, Hawaii. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, outdoors and palm trees.

node.text: I spent the last few months planning what was supposed to be an epic one in one experience with Chloe out of the country that didn’t happen bc of 😷☹️. On Wednesday (with a ton of amazing suggestions from friends) we pivoted to what’s so far been magical surfing, snorkeling and a bunch of surprising adventures in store the next few days. I love a plan, but try to remind myself that the best moments happen when you least expect them! 🐠🌺🌴

node.text:
CHOCOLATE CHIP GRANOLA BARS! 🍫 Planned an entire vacation in 24 hours and taking off in minutes with 4 of these beauties in my bag! The most delicious travel or back to school snack you can make! Guess where we’re headed? 👉🏻recipe link in bio👈🏻⁣
⁣
https://weelicious.com/chocolate-chip-granola-bars/

node.text: It's basically like a 12 minute risotto without the need to stir it. The easiest way to get even vegetable resistant kids to WANT to eat them because each bite has confetti like pieces of carrot and broccoli with tons of of flavors in every bite. What other vegetable would you want to add in? 🌶🫑 Recipe link in bio! https://weelicious.com/carrot-broccoli-cheese-orzo/

node.text:
No shame in the TUNA PASTA SALAD game! I didn’t even know my girls liked tuna until a few months ago?! What have I been waiting for?! I made this (affordable) beauty in under 20 minutes for a poolside play date dinner and everyone crushed it (especially with the secret ingredient in every bite 🤫 What’s the fastest, most satisfying meal you’ve been making? ⁣
⁣
👉🏻Recipe link in bio 👈🏻 ⁣
⁣
https://weelicious.com/tuna-pasta-salad/
